ğŸ§± Key component: The Dockerfile
1ï¸âƒ£ Script for assembly: A Dockerfile is a script that contains instructions used by Docker to build a Docker image. It specifies the base image, dependencies, and steps needed to create the final image. ğŸ“œ
2ï¸âƒ£ Layered approach: Docker uses a layered file system to build images. Each instruction in a Dockerfile adds a new layer to the image. This approach makes it easier to track changes and update specific parts of the image without rebuilding the entire thing. ğŸ§±
