ğŸ—ï¸ Building an image:
1ï¸âƒ£ Create a Dockerfile: This file defines your application's environment in Docker. It includes instructions to install dependencies, set environment variables, and run your application.ğŸ³
2ï¸âƒ£ Build the image: To create a Docker image from your Dockerfile, use the `docker build` command. This command builds an image based on the instructions in your Dockerfile and tags it with a specified name (using the `-t` flag). ğŸ› ï¸
