ğŸ“‹ Inspecting images and layers:
1ï¸âƒ£ List images: Use the command `docker image ls` to see a list of all the images on your system. ğŸ“‹
2ï¸âƒ£ View individual layers: To view the individual layers of a specific image, use `docker history your-image-name` or `docker inspect your-image-name`. ğŸ”
3ï¸âƒ£ Remove an image: If you no longer need an image, you can remove it using `docker image rm your-image-name`. âŒ
